Module 6: Python Fundamentals – THEORY SOLUTIONS
1. Introduction to Python
Theory:

Q1 Introduction to Python and its features (simple, high-level, interpreted language).
A. Python is a high-level, interpreted, general-purpose programming language created by Guido van Rossum.
Features of Python:
Simple and easy to learn
High-level language
Interpreted (no need to compile)
Platform independent
Large standard library
Supports object-oriented programming
Open-source and free.

Q2. History and evolution of Python.

A. Developed by Guido van Rossum in 1991
Named after the TV show “Monty Python’s Flying Circus”
Python 2 released in 2000
Python 3 released in 2008 (current standard)

Q3 Advantages of Python Over Other programming  Languages
A. Easy syntax
Faster development
Large community support
Used in AI, ML, Web, Data Science
Fewer lines of code compared to C/C++

Q4 Installing Python and setting up the development environment (Anaconda, PyCharm, or VS Code).
A. Anaconda
PyCharm
VS Code
Jupyter Notebook

Q.5 Writing and executing your first Python program.
A. A Python program is written in a .py file and executed using:
Copy code
Bash
python filename.py
Example:
Copy code
Python
print("Hello World")

