2. Programming Style
Theory:

Q1 Understanding Python’s PEP 8 guidelines.
A. PEP 8 is the official style guide for Python code.
Rules:
Use proper indentation (4 spaces)
Meaningful variable names
Line length ≤ 79 characters
Use comments properly

Q2 Indentation, comments, and naming conventions in Python.

A. Python uses indentation instead of braces
Comments start with #
Variables should use snake_case
Example:
Copy code
Python
total_marks = 90  # storing marks

Q3 Writing readable and maintainable code.
A. Readable code:
Easy to understand
Easy to debug
Easy to modify

Lab:
Q1:
A.
user_name = "Vishal"
user_age = 21
print("Name:",user_name )
print("Age:",user_age )

